revision.text:
'''宣旨'''（'''せんじ'''）は朝廷が出す命令書の形態の一つ。[[太政官符]]が組織名義で出されるのに対し、[[天皇]]個人の名義で出される書類。事実上の勅令書。[[律令制]]においては最高の命令書。[[摂関政治]]が行われている間も形式上は天皇の命令で出されていたため、これが使われた。[[院政]]期に入って以来、次第に効力を失い[[院宣]]に取って代わられた。
主な例としては鎌倉時代の後白河法皇による源義経へ出された源頼朝追討の宣旨がある。
[[Category:日本の律令制|せんし]] {{history-stub}}

'''宣旨'''（'''せんじ'''）は朝廷が出す命令書の形態の一つ。[[太政官符]]が組織名義で出されるのに対し、[[天皇]]個人の名義で出される書類。事実上の勅令書。[[律令制]]においては最高の命令書。[[摂関政治]]が行われている間も形式上は天皇の命令で出されていたため、これが使われた。[[院政]]期に入って以来、次第に効力を失い[[院宣]]に取って代わられた（主な例としては鎌倉時代の後白河法皇による源義経へ出された源頼朝追討の院宣がある）。
==関連項目== *[[院宣]] *[[綸旨]] *[[令旨]] *[[太政官符]]
[[Category:日本の律令制|せんし]] {{history-stub}}

{{otheruses|{{ill|Imperial edicts and official documents|ja|天皇|12=draft|12=draft}} or oral orders by aristocrats|The title of a senior female servant or {{ill|nyōbō|ja|女房|12=draft|12=draft}}|{{ill|Senji (official position)|ja|宣旨 (役職)|12=draft|12=draft}}}} '''Senji''' (宣旨) refers to the format of documents used to transmit the orders of the {{ill|Emperor of Japan|ja|天皇|12=draft|12=draft}} or the {{ill|Daijōkan|ja|太政官|12=draft|12=draft}} in post-{{ill|Ritsuryō period|ja|律令期|12=draft|12=draft}} Japan. It is one of the document forms issued by the imperial court, a variant of {{ill|Imperial decrees|ja|詔勅|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Overview == The {{ill|Emperor of Japan|ja|天皇|12=draft|12=draft}}'s orders or intentions ({{ill|Chokushi|ja|勅旨|12=draft|12=draft}}) were transcribed into documents such as {{ill|Daijōkanpu|ja|太政官符|12=draft|12=draft}} and {{ill|Daijōkanchō|ja|太政官牒|12=draft|12=draft}} by the {{ill|Benkankyoku|ja|弁官局|12=draft|12=draft}}, with {{ill|Shi (Ritsuryō)|ja|史 (律令制)|12=draft|12=draft}} staff receiving the emperor's commands orally. To avoid forgetting the orders, scribes created personal notes, which gradually evolved into formalized documents called Senji. While only the signatures of the scribe and other officials appeared on the documents, they were recognized as reflecting the emperor’s will. This conferred authority on unsigned documents, occasionally leading to the issuance of {{ill|Fake imperial edicts|ja|偽勅|12=draft|12=draft}} in the {{ill|Bakumatsu|ja|幕末|12=draft|12=draft}} period.
Initially, imperial commands were issued as {{ill|Imperial edicts|ja|詔書|12=draft|12=draft}} or {{ill|Chokushi|ja|勅旨|12=draft|12=draft}}, which were reserved for significant matters and strictly regulated in form. To allow for greater flexibility, the Senji format was introduced.
=== Issuance Procedure === The issuance procedure involved conveying the emperor's command through the {{ill|Naishi no Tsukasa|ja|内侍司|12=draft|12=draft}}, followed by the {{ill|Kurododokoro|ja|蔵人頭|12=draft|12=draft}}, and then to the appointed {{ill|Jōkyō|ja|上卿|12=draft|12=draft}}. The Jōkyō would transmit it to relevant offices, including the {{ill|Geki-kyoku|ja|外記局|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Benkankyoku|ja|弁官|12=draft|12=draft}}, and {{ill|Naiki-kyoku|ja|内記局|12=draft|12=draft}}, which would draft the Senji. This process began during the {{ill|Kōnin era|ja|弘仁|12=draft|12=draft}} (810–824). Commands passed from the Naishi to the Kurododokoro were called {{ill|Naishi-sen|ja|内侍宣|12=draft|12=draft}} and later evolved into {{ill|Nyōbō Hōsho|ja|女房奉書|12=draft|12=draft}} in the {{ill|Kamakura period|ja|鎌倉時代|12=draft|12=draft}}. Oral orders from the Kurododokoro to the Jōkyō, known as {{ill|Kusenshō|ja|口宣|12=draft|12=draft}}, were later documented and su11lemented with {{ill|Kusenshō-an|ja|口宣案|12=draft|12=draft}} as drafts.
By the {{ill|Heian period|ja|平安時代|12=draft|12=draft}}, Senji issued by the {{ill|Geki-kyoku|ja|外記局|12=draft|12=draft}} in their name were recognized. Additionally, documents issued by the Benkankyoku on the order of high-ranking officials ({{ill|Kugyō|ja|Kugyō|1=Kugyō|12=draft|12=draft}}) instead of the {{ill|Daijōkanpu|ja|太政官符|12=draft|12=draft}} were called {{ill|Kan-senji|ja|官宣旨|12=draft|12=draft}}.
=== Examples of Senji === Examples of Senji include:
* '''Concurrent Official Appointment (Yamakai-ki)''': 内大臣藤原朝臣 正二位行大納言源朝臣雅通宣 奉 勅、件人宜如旧兼任右近大将者 仁安二年二月十一日 大外記 (Translation): Minister of the Interior Fujiwara no Ason declares: By imperial decree, the aforementioned person is to continue serving concurrently as Ukon no Dainagon. February 11, 1167, by the Great External Scribe.
* '''Acting Regent Senji (Koryū-ki)''': 正二位行権大納言兼太皇太后宮大夫藤原朝臣公任宣 奉 勅、除目等雑事、宜令左大臣准摂政儀行之者 長和四年十月廿七日 大外記小野朝臣文義奉 (Translation): Senior Second Rank Acting Chancellor and Minister to the Dowager Empress' Palace Fujiwara no Ason Kintō declares: By imperial decree, the Left Minister shall perform the duties of a regent for appointments and miscellaneous matters. October 27, 1015, by the Great External Scribe Ono no Ason Fumiyoshi.
=== Types of Senji === {{section-stub}}
== Insei and Rinji == {{main|{{ill|Insen|ja|院宣|12=draft|12=draft}}|{{ill|Rinji|ja|綸旨|12=draft|12=draft}}}} During the {{ill|Insei|ja|院政|12=draft|12=draft}} period and the subsequent {{ill|Kamakura period|ja|鎌倉時代|12=draft|12=draft}}, the issuance of {{ill|Insen|ja|院宣|12=draft|12=draft}} exceeded Senji. Additionally, {{ill|Rinji|ja|綸旨|12=draft|12=draft}}, a simplified form of Senji, became more common. == See Also == * {{ill|Imperial decrees|ja|詔勅|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Insen|ja|院宣|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Rinji|ja|綸旨|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Reijishi|ja|令旨|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Gokyōsho|ja|御教書|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Gonaisho|ja|御内書|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Uda Insenji|ja|宇多院宣旨|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Juei 2nd Year Tenth Month Senji|ja|寿永二年十月宣旨|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Juei 3rd Year Senji|ja|寿永三年宣旨|12=draft|12=draft}} * {{ill|Kobunsho|ja|古文書|12=draft|12=draft}}
== Further Reading == * Shohachi Hayakawa, *Senji Shiron*, Iwanami Shoten, April 1990, ISBN 4-00-001193-6.
{{Japanese-history-stub}}
