=== Issuance Procedure === The issuance procedure involved conveying the emperor's command through the {{ill|Naishi no Tsukasa|ja|内侍司|12=draft|12=draft}}, followed by the {{ill|Kurododokoro|ja|蔵人頭|12=draft|12=draft}}, and then to the appointed {{ill|Jōkyō|ja|上卿|12=draft|12=draft}}. The Jōkyō would transmit it to relevant offices, including the {{ill|Geki-kyoku|ja|外記局|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Benkankyoku|ja|弁官|12=draft|12=draft}}, and {{ill|Naiki-kyoku|ja|内記局|12=draft|12=draft}}, which would draft the Senji. This process began during the {{ill|Kōnin era|ja|弘仁|12=draft|12=draft}} (810–824). Commands passed from the Naishi to the Kurododokoro were called {{ill|Naishi-sen|ja|内侍宣|12=draft|12=draft}} and later evolved into {{ill|Nyōbō Hōsho|ja|女房奉書|12=draft|12=draft}} in the {{ill|Kamakura period|ja|鎌倉時代|12=draft|12=draft}}. Oral orders from the Kurododokoro to the Jōkyō, known as {{ill|Kusenshō|ja|口宣|12=draft|12=draft}}, were later documented and su11lemented with {{ill|Kusenshō-an|ja|口宣案|12=draft|12=draft}} as drafts.
By the {{ill|Heian period|ja|平安時代|12=draft|12=draft}}, Senji issued by the {{ill|Geki-kyoku|ja|外記局|12=draft|12=draft}} in their name were recognized. Additionally, documents issued by the Benkankyoku on the order of high-Ranking officials ({{ill|Kugyō|ja|Kugyō|1=Kugyō|12=draft|12=draft}}) instead of the {{ill|Daijōkanpu|ja|太政官符|12=draft|12=draft}} were called {{ill|Kan-senji|ja|官宣旨|12=draft|12=draft}}.
=== Examples of Senji === Examples of Senji include:
* '''Concurrent Official Appointment (Yamakai-ki)''': 内大臣藤原朝臣 正二位行大納言源朝臣雅通宣 奉 勅、件人宜如旧兼任右近大将者 仁安二年二月十一日 大外記 (Translation): Minister of the Interior Fujiwara no Ason declares: By imperial decree, the aforementioned person is to continue serving concurrently as Ukon no Dainagon. February 11, 1167, by the Great External Scribe.
* '''Acting Regent Senji (Koryū-ki)''': 正二位行権大納言兼太皇太后宮大夫藤原朝臣公任宣 奉 勅、除目等雑事、宜令左大臣准摂政儀行之者 長和四年十月廿七日 大外記小野朝臣文義奉 (Translation): Senior Second Rank Acting Chancellor and Minister to the Dowager Empress' Palace Fujiwara no Ason Kintō declares: By imperial decree, the Left Minister shall perform the duties of a regent for appointments and miscellaneous matters. October 27, 1015, by the Great External Scribe Ono no Ason Fumiyoshi.
=== Types of Senji === {{section-stub}}
