Initially, imperial commands were issued as {{ill|Imperial edicts|ja|詔書|qq=draft|qq=draft}} or {{ill|Chokushi|ja|勅旨|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, which were reserved for significant matters and strictly regulated in form. To allow for greater flexibility, the Senji format was introduced.
=== Issuance Procedure === The issuance procedure involved conveying the emperor's command through the {{ill|Naishi no Tsukasa|ja|内侍司|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, followed by the {{ill|Kurododokoro|ja|蔵人頭|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, and then to the appointed {{ill|Jōkyō|ja|上卿|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. The Jōkyō would transmit it to relevant offices, including the {{ill|Geki-kyoku|ja|外記局|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Benkankyoku|ja|弁官|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, and {{ill|Naiki-kyoku|ja|内記局|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, which would draft the Senji. This process began during the {{ill|Kōnin era|ja|弘仁|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (810–824). Commands passed from the Naishi to the Kurododokoro were called {{ill|Naishi-sen|ja|内侍宣|qq=draft|qq=draft}} and later evolved into {{ill|Nyōbō Hōsho|ja|女房奉書|qq=draft|qq=draft}} in the {{ill|Kamakura period|ja|鎌倉時代|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. Oral orders from the Kurododokoro to the Jōkyō, known as {{ill|Kusenshō|ja|口宣|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, were later documented and su11lemented with {{ill|Kusenshō-an|ja|口宣案|qq=draft|qq=draft}} as drafts.
By the {{ill|Heian period|ja|平安時代|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, Senji issued by the {{ill|Geki-kyoku|ja|外記局|qq=draft|qq=draft}} in their name were recognized. Additionally, documents issued by the Benkankyoku on the order of high-Ranking officials ({{ill|Kugyō|ja|Kugyō|1=Kugyō|qq=draft|qq=draft}}) instead of the {{ill|Daijōkanpu|ja|太政官符|qq=draft|qq=draft}} were called {{ill|Kan-senji|ja|官宣旨|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
=== Examples of Senji === Examples of Senji include:
* '''Concurrent Official Appointment (Yamakai-ki)''': 内大臣藤原朝臣 正二位行大納言源朝臣雅通宣 奉 勅、件人宜如旧兼任右近大将者 仁安二年二月十一日 大外記 (Translation): Minister of the Interior Fujiwara no Ason declares: By imperial decree, the aforementioned person is to continue serving concurrently as Ukon no Dainagon. February 11, 1167, by the Great External Scribe.
* '''Acting Regent Senji (Koryū-ki)''': 正二位行権大納言兼太皇太后宮大夫藤原朝臣公任宣 奉 勅、除目等雑事、宜令左大臣准摂政儀行之者 長和四年十月廿七日 大外記小野朝臣文義奉 (Translation): Senior Second Rank Acting Chancellor and Minister to the Dowager Empress' Palace Fujiwara no Ason Kintō declares: By imperial decree, the Left Minister shall perform the duties of a regent for appointments and miscellaneous matters. October 27, 1015, by the Great External Scribe Ono no Ason Fumiyoshi.
=== Types of Senji === {{section-stub}}
== Insei and Rinji == {{main|{{ill|Insen|ja|院宣|qq=draft|qq=draft}}|{{ill|Rinji|ja|綸旨|qq=draft|qq=draft}}}} During the {{ill|Insei|ja|院政|qq=draft|qq=draft}} period and the subsequent {{ill|Kamakura period|ja|鎌倉時代|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, the issuance of {{ill|Insen|ja|院宣|qq=draft|qq=draft}} exceeded Senji. Additionally, {{ill|Rinji|ja|綸旨|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, a simplified form of Senji, became more common. == See Also == * {{ill|Imperial decrees|ja|詔勅|qq=draft|qq=draft}} * {{ill|Insen|ja|院宣|qq=draft|qq=draft}} * {{ill|Rinji|ja|綸旨|qq=draft|qq=draft}} * {{ill|Reijishi|ja|令旨|qq=draft|qq=draft}} * {{ill|Gokyōsho|ja|御教書|qq=draft|qq=draft}} * {{ill|Gonaisho|ja|御内書|qq=draft|qq=draft}} * {{ill|Uda Insenji|ja|宇多院宣旨|qq=draft|qq=draft}} * {{ill|Juei 2nd Year Tenth Month Senji|ja|寿永二年十月宣旨|qq=draft|qq=draft}} * {{ill|Juei 3rd Year Senji|ja|寿永三年宣旨|qq=draft|qq=draft}} * {{ill|Kobunsho|ja|古文書|qq=draft|qq=draft}}
== Further Reading == * Shohachi Hayakawa, *Senji Shiron*, Iwanami Shoten, April 1990, ISBN 4-00-001193-6.
